net.java.jddac.common.fblock
Class Entity

java.lang.Object
  net.java.jddac.common.fblock.Entity
All Implemented Interfaces:
ConfigurationInterface
Direct Known Subclasses:
ArgStore, FunctionBlock, Service
public abstract class Entity
extends java.lang.Object
implements ConfigurationInterface

Represents the Entity concept from IEEE 1451.1. Entity is a network visible (and addressable) object. It is an abtract class and not meant to be instantiated.

configure

public void configure(ArgArray configuration)
               throws java.lang.Exception
Description copied from interface: ConfigurationInterface
Provides a method to configure object properties. The registry argument contains an ArgArray composed named values. Any values that are not specified are assumed to be left unchanged. That is, if a value is not present, do not assume it means 0 or true or some other default. This allows the configure method to be used to set a single value without affecting other values.

Specified by:
configure in interface ConfigurationInterface
Parameters:
configuration - contains incoming configuration parameters as named values.

Name Default Description
className N/A Class of the object, including the entire package name.
instanceName N/A instance name of this object. If supplied, there must be a name supplied. A null entry will result in an exception.
Entity.owningBlockObject unknown instance name of the Block which owns this entity. For most cases, this entry can be safely left blank.
Entity.description unknown Human readable string
Throws:
java.lang.Exception
